commit.message:
Fix exception on corrupt JPEG files

It happens in rare cases when ord receives an empty byte string

Fix handling of different path types

In Python, a path can normally be either type bytes, str, or
pathlib.Path. Coercing a bytes object to str results in using the repr
value.

Add tests for all path types.

Remove deprecated use of 'setup.py test'

Since setuptools v41.5.0 (27 Oct 2019), the 'test' command is formally
deprecated and should not be used. Now use unittest as the test entry
point.

Add tests for the getDPI() function

The test revealed str/bytes mixups in Python 3. They have been fixed.
Fix error on long float number
Add Python 3.8 and 3.9 to the test matrix
Added support for little endian BigTIFF
Allow comments on binary Netpbm files
Fix handling of invalid char after width on Netpbm
Changes: hasattr(filepath, 'read') to isinstance(filepath, io.BytesIO) in imagesize.py, requests.get to urllib.request.urlopen in test/test_get_filelike.py [requsets package no longer needed]
Update to handle in-memory filelike objects
Update to handle in-memory filelike objects

Added Arm64 jobs in Travis-CI
